AB  - Feehan (1992) established some rules for public input provision in a model where the tariff revenue is utilized to fund public inputs. According to these rules Feehan discussed whether the public input would be produced at a larger amount than the level that maximizes the national income. This note sharpens the result of Feehan by using information regarding Lagrangian multipliers.
