KW  - International debt
KW  - Increasing returns
KW  - Growth
AB  - A growth model of international borrowing subject to a credit constraint is developed for an economy with increasing returns to capital. Unlike constant-returns models, the equilibrium credit constraint as a share of the capital stock is increasing in the capital stock. Increasing returns also enhance the potential for ‘long-term’ lending strategies, which may be related to rescheduling and concerted lending. Using simulations with parameter values that do not favor these strategies under constant returns, we show that a long-term lending strategy may dominate a myopic lending strategy.
